 To find the value of $b$ that satisfies the equation $161_{b}+134_{b}=315_{b}$, we need to convert each of the base-$b$ numbers to base 10 and then solve for $b$.</think>
<u>First, convert $161_{b}$ to base 10:</u>
\begin{align*}
161_{b}&=1\cdot b^{2}+6\cdot b^{1}+1\cdot b^{0}\\
&=b^{2}+6b+1
\end{align*}
<u>Now, convert $134_{b}$ to base 10:</u>
\begin{align*}
134_{b}&=1\cdot b^{2}+3\cdot b^{1}+4\cdot b^{0}\\
&=b^{2}+3b+4
\end{align*}
<u>Then, convert $315_{b}$ to base 10:</u>
\begin{align*}
315_{b}&=3\cdot b^{2}+1\cdot b^{1}+5\cdot b^{0}\\
&=3b^{2}+b+5
\end{align*}
<u>Now, solve the equation $161_{b}+134_{b}=315_{b}$:</u>
\begin{align*}
(b^{2}+6b+1)+(b^{2}+3b+4)&=3b^{2}+b+5\\
2b^{2}+9b+5&=3b^{2}+b+5\\
2b^{2}+9b+5-3b^{2}-b-5&=3b^{2}+b+5-3b^{2}-b-5\\
-b^{2}+8b&=0\\
b(-b+8)&=0\\
\end{align*}
The solutions to the equation are $b=0$ and $b=8$. However, the base of a number must be greater than 1 and less than or equal to 10 (depending on the number of digits in the base-$b$ number), so the only valid solution is $b=8$.</answer>

